name: First Industrial Robot
description: The first invention of a industrial robot was made by George Charles Devol.  He is
often called the father of robotics. He built his robot in 1954 but was not produced until 1961
in a General Motors factory for die casting and handling and spot welding, and was controlled by
a magnetic drum

name: Tentacle Arm
placeName: The first tentacle arm was made
description: Just a few years after the first robot is put on the first factories, the first
octupus arm tentacle is made.  It was made in 1968 by Marvin Minsky.  This arm had twelve joints
and could be controlled PDP-6 computer or a via joystick.

name: Shakey
description: The first mobile robot was created by Charles Rosen.  Shakey (robot alias)
performed tasks that required planning and route finding and was even known as the first electronic
person

name: Change
description: The first electromagnetic robot changed the way robots functioned going forward.

name: Robotics in Industry
description: In industry robots with small computers were made to fabricate motorcycle frames.
While other robots were precision insertion robots and fully electric microprocessing robots for manufacturing.

name: NASA
description: NASA works on first space probe with a robotic arm.
First motor driven robots.

name: Gantry Robots
description: Gantry robots replace older factory robot models due
to more dynamic movement capabilities and safer operations.

name: Motoman
description: Motoman developed two robots that can be ontrolled by one peripeheral

name: Rover Mission
description: Mars exploration rover mission is conducted by two robots

name: Light Wieght Robots
description: Germans invent light weight robots out of aluminum with increased sensitivity.

name: Mainstream Robots in Industry
description: Increased productivity and mainstream industry utilization of robots
NASA launches first humanoid robot on a mission.
